Available Tools: get_historical_readings | get_average_reading | get_min_max | export_sensor_data
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "sensor_id": "string", "from": "string", "to": "string", "interval": "string" }
Response Schema: { "sensor_id": "string", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "string", "value": number }], "avg": number, "min": number, "max": number }
---
Question: Get the hourly temperature readings for sensor TEMP-001 in the warehouse from yesterday morning until noon.
Call: { "func_call": "get_historical_readings", "sensor_id": "TEMP-001", "from": "2023-10-24T08:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-24T12:00:00Z", "interval": "hourly" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "TEMP-001", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "2023-10-24T08:00:00Z", "value": 21.4 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-24T09:00:00Z", "value": 22.1 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-24T10:00:00Z", "value": 22.8 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-24T11:00:00Z", "value": 23.2 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-24T12:00:00Z", "value": 23.5 }], "avg": 22.6, "min": 21.4, "max": 23.5 }

